originalText.text: My wife and I had both our motorcycles there for over 15yrs until we moved them upstate a few years ago.  The garage is kept clean, the security of the garage is top notch.  I never had any problems having the bikes there for all those years.   The owners are extremely helpful if you need anything. Since they ride themselves, their passion about motorcycles goes far beyond a normal garage owner.  It’s not just a business for them.

originalText.text: Secure (and super cool) garage owned by awesome people. If you have a bike and are parking indoors in the EV, then you're definitely an enthusiast; this place attracts a great community of down-to-earth, respectful riders. Power at ever bike and storage for your own tools, parts, gear, etc. is a huge benefit over parking at a generic garage.

originalText.text: Bike was parked for a few months over winter and into the pandemic lockdown.  While everyone was super stressed and kinda awful Michael helped me drain the bad gas and get it going. Riding was the only thing that kept me sane
